&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit , a highly motivated and experienced BCG Immunisation nurse to join our current Paediatric BCG Immunisation Service,for a fixed term contract of six (6) months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will be delivering the Paediatric BCG programme within the NELFT four(4) London boroughs of Barking &amp; Dagenham, Havering, Redbridge and Waltham Forest to neonates and infants who are who are eligible for the vaccine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide a high quality immunisation service, must have attention to detail, passionate about improving quality, safety standards and patient experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our friendly team consists of BCG immunisation nurses and support staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have the right skills to meet requirements of the post, we look forward to hearing from you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
